Singapore hotelsâ€™ performance slipped sequentially in October  following highs in September when the Formula 1 (F1) night race came to town  Singapore Tourism Board (STB) data showed on Friday (Nov 29). This came even as international visitor arrivals picked up for the month. The average room rate (ARR) dropped sequentially to S$275.19 last month  down 12.9 per cent from S$315.79 in the preceding month. Still  it was up 1.7 per cent year on year (yoy)..

The Peopleâ€™s Bank of China conducted US$111 billion of outright reverse repurchase agreements in November  it said in a statement on Friday (Nov 29). The contracts are for three months and are aimed at safeguarding reasonably ample liquidity in the banking system  according to the statement. That exceeded the 500 billion yuan (S$92.5 billion) injected last month.
